    • Method Detail

      • splitString

        public void splitString​()
        Method used to split the string base on various conditions; commas , white spaces or both. The values are then placed individually into a stack until a mathematical operator is reached and the following operation if performed on the previous two numbers there were in the stack by popping them and push the result back into the stack. If an invalid character is reached or the infix mathematical formula is erroneous an error message will be prompted.
